cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on verifying security properties of C code for cryptographic protocols.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of contracts and annotations in C code.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper formalizes the symbolic model in Coq.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a general-purpose verifier to prove security properties.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses formal algebraic terms and symbolic terms in the verification process.
